In .NET MAUI, use `Application.Current.RequestedTheme` and the `RequestedThemeChanged` event. To override, set `Application.Current.UserAppTheme`.

```csharp
// Detect current system theme
AppTheme currentTheme = Application.Current.RequestedTheme;
// Returns AppTheme.Light, AppTheme.Dark, or AppTheme.Unspecified

// Subscribe to real-time theme changes
Application.Current.RequestedThemeChanged += (s, e) =>
{
    AppTheme newTheme = e.RequestedTheme;
    Debug.WriteLine($"Theme changed to: {newTheme}");
    // Update UI or trigger re-theming logic here
};

// Force a specific theme (overrides system setting)
Application.Current.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Dark;

// Revert to following the system setting
Application.Current.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Unspecified;
```

**In XAML**, use `AppThemeBinding` for automatic resource switching:

```xml
<Label Text="Hello"
       TextColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=Black, Dark=White}" />

<ContentPage BackgroundColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=#FFFFFF, Dark=#1E1E1E}">
```

**For a full theme service** you can inject across your app:

```csharp
public class ThemeService
{
    public event Action<AppTheme>? ThemeChanged;

    public ThemeService()
    {
        Application.Current!.RequestedThemeChanged += (_, e) =>
        {
            if (Application.Current.UserAppTheme == AppTheme.Unspecified)
                ThemeChanged?.Invoke(e.RequestedTheme);
        };
    }

    public AppTheme Current =>
        Application.Current!.UserAppTheme != AppTheme.Unspecified
            ? Application.Current.UserAppTheme
            : Application.Current.RequestedTheme;

    public void SetTheme(AppTheme theme)
    {
        Application.Current!.UserAppTheme = theme;
        ThemeChanged?.Invoke(Current);
    }

    public void FollowSystem()
    {
        Application.Current!.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Unspecified;
        ThemeChanged?.Invoke(Current);
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

| API | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `RequestedTheme` | Read the OS-level theme |
| `RequestedThemeChanged` | React when the OS theme toggles |
| `UserAppTheme` | Override with a specific theme |
| `AppThemeBinding` | XAML-side automatic resource swap |

Set `UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Unspecified` to resume following the system. The `RequestedThemeChanged` event fires on the main thread, so you can update UI directly in the handler.
